01:53.800 --> 01:57.800
Dad? Dad?

02:05.800 --> 02:07.800
How is he?

02:09.800 --> 02:10.800
He's fine, aye.

02:12.800 --> 02:14.800
Nobody ever died of a lost memory.

02:18.800 --> 02:19.750
Are you ready for this, Dimarco?

02:19.800 --> 02:20.800
Born for it.

02:21.800 --> 02:23.750
You, Sarge?

02:23.800 --> 02:25.750
Aye. Let's go.

02:25.800 --> 02:27.750
Let's get this done.

02:27.800 --> 02:29.000
This one's for Nick Page.

02:40.800 --> 02:42.800
Where are you going?

02:48.800 --> 02:50.750
Work.

02:50.800 --> 02:51.800
Where's Mummy?

02:54.800 --> 02:57.750
She's in hospital having the baby.

02:57.800 --> 02:59.750
Yusra will look after you.

02:59.800 --> 03:02.750
Is the baby going to live here?

03:03.800 --> 03:07.800
Yes. You, me, Mummy and the baby.

03:12.800 --> 03:14.800
We can play soldiers when I get back.

03:16.800 --> 03:17.800
Promise?

03:19.800 --> 03:21.800
On parade 1800 hours, Corporal Markham.

03:23.800 --> 03:24.800
Mmm.

03:29.800 --> 03:31.750
Back to sleep.

03:39.800 --> 03:41.750
Oh, no. What time is it?

03:41.800 --> 03:43.750
Early.

03:43.800 --> 03:46.750
A good wife would have
been... would have been up

03:46.800 --> 03:49.750
and cooked her husband breakfast.

03:49.800 --> 03:52.800
You've got seven minutes.

03:54.800 --> 03:56.750
What time will you be home?

03:56.800 --> 04:01.750
I'm not sure. It's best if
you don't know too much.

04:01.800 --> 04:03.750
But you'll be home for tea?

04:03.800 --> 04:06.750
Hmm? Mmm, mm-hmm.

04:06.800 --> 04:08.750
What shall I make?

04:08.800 --> 04:10.800
Ah, you decide.

04:14.800 --> 04:15.750
It's not plugged in.

04:15.800 --> 04:17.750
Oh, it won't take too long.

04:17.800 --> 04:19.750
I have to go. Mmm.

04:19.800 --> 04:20.800
Sorry.

04:23.800 --> 04:26.750
Corporal Stoneham, he
says it is time to go.

04:40.800 --> 04:42.750
Look after him.

04:42.800 --> 04:43.800
Of course.

05:02.800 --> 05:03.650
Terribly sorry.

05:08.800 --> 05:12.750
Aden, where East meets West --

05:12.800 --> 05:14.750
vital as an oil refinery,

05:14.800 --> 05:16.200
as well as a Gulf trade route.

05:17.800 --> 05:20.750
The beach here at Aden is lovely.

05:20.800 --> 05:22.750
The sand is warm, and the sharks

05:22.800 --> 05:23.900
are not always hungry.

05:30.800 --> 05:32.750
The occasional outbreaks
of violence are caused by

05:32.800 --> 05:35.800
what are officially called
dissident tribesmen.

05:37.800 --> 05:40.800
As long as there's trouble,
there must be troops.

05:41.800 --> 05:44.750
The Queen has full
confidence in Aden's future,

05:44.800 --> 05:48.800
describing it as the perfect
example of Colonial rule.

06:04.800 --> 06:09.750
The raid party will be landing as I
speak, including Baxter and Dimarco.

06:09.800 --> 06:13.750
Their objective -- to capture one man.

06:13.800 --> 06:16.750
The target's code name is Starfish.

06:16.800 --> 06:20.750
He's brutal, he's clever...

06:20.800 --> 06:22.750
His real name is Abdul Kadir Hakim,

06:22.800 --> 06:27.750
and we believe he's responsible
for the murder of Captain Page.

06:27.800 --> 06:29.750
Now, we've received intelligence
that Starfish will be at a remote

06:29.800 --> 06:34.750
farmhouse here, which the raid
party will storm at 1300 hours.

06:34.800 --> 06:36.750
Our job is to rendezvous
upcountry with the raid party

06:36.800 --> 06:39.750
on the other side of the mountain,
where they'll be handing

06:39.800 --> 06:42.750
Starfish over to us for escort back here.

06:42.800 --> 06:45.750
We'll be in two Land
Rovers travelling in convoy.

06:45.800 --> 06:47.750
Captain Martin will command
the second Land Rover.

06:47.800 --> 06:50.800
Now, we'll have to use the
Dhala Road, I'm afraid.

06:55.800 --> 06:57.800
We've no choice about the route.

06:58.800 --> 06:59.900
Just seven miles of it.

07:00.800 --> 07:04.750
We will maintain complete radio
silence from the moment we leave

07:04.800 --> 07:07.750
this base, and it stays that way
until we return with the prisoner.

07:07.800 --> 07:10.750
This operation cannot be compromised.

07:10.800 --> 07:14.750
If one Land Rover gets into
bother, the orders are clear --

07:14.800 --> 07:17.750
the other continues to the
rendezvous at all costs, sir.

07:17.800 --> 07:19.750
(If we make it that far.)

07:19.800 --> 07:21.750
What's that, Stoneham?

07:21.800 --> 07:23.750
Nothing, sir. Sorry, sir.

07:23.800 --> 07:24.800
Good.

07:26.800 --> 07:29.750
Oh, one more thing, erm...

07:29.800 --> 07:31.750
There's a reporter coming with us,

07:31.800 --> 07:34.750
so tomorrow the world will
know what a damn good job

07:34.800 --> 07:35.750
the Royal Military Police is doing.

07:35.800 --> 07:36.750
- Sir.
- Sir.

07:36.800 --> 07:38.750
Prepare the vehicles.
Await my orders to leave.

07:38.800 --> 07:40.800
Dismissed.

07:45.800 --> 07:46.750
Sir?

07:46.800 --> 07:48.750
Orchover?

07:48.800 --> 07:50.800
Is it a girl or boy?

07:52.800 --> 07:53.750
Erm...

07:53.800 --> 07:56.750
No news yet. We don't know.

08:06.800 --> 08:09.750
I'm afraid I don't think
there's time for that.

08:09.800 --> 08:13.750
Cleanliness is next to
godliness. I make the rules here.

08:35.799 --> 08:40.750
[Left, right, left,
right, left, right, left!]

08:40.799 --> 08:43.799
[Left, right, left,
right, left, right, left!]

08:59.800 --> 09:03.300
♪ Love letters straight from... ♪

09:04.800 --> 09:07.750
[Help! Help!]

09:11.800 --> 09:12.800
[Help!]

09:15.800 --> 09:21.750
Help! HELP!

09:21.800 --> 09:22.800
Help!

09:49.800 --> 09:51.750
I like your nightie.

09:51.800 --> 09:53.750
Oh, er, it's...

09:53.800 --> 09:55.750
Frilly.

09:55.800 --> 09:56.800
Yes.

10:09.800 --> 10:12.750
Is he good at fucking?

10:12.800 --> 10:14.000
Your handsome husband.

10:15.800 --> 10:16.800
Oh...

10:17.800 --> 10:20.750
Why aren't the raid party
bringing in Starfish themselves?

10:20.800 --> 10:22.750
They're on foot.

10:22.800 --> 10:23.800
Why?

10:25.800 --> 10:26.750
It was going to be 1 Para,

10:26.800 --> 10:31.750
but the terrain makes a
parachute drop impossible,

10:31.800 --> 10:33.750
and the chopper's too noisy,

10:33.800 --> 10:35.800
so it's a speed-march in from the coast.

10:37.800 --> 10:39.000
Royal Marine Commandos?

10:40.800 --> 10:43.750
Oh. They do exist, then.

10:43.800 --> 10:46.750
It's a great honour for any
member of this regiment to serve

10:46.800 --> 10:47.750
with the SAS.

10:47.800 --> 10:50.750
Captain Page was halfway between
leaving us and joining them

10:50.800 --> 10:51.750
when he was killed.

10:51.800 --> 10:54.750
They've asked for us to do this with them.

10:54.800 --> 10:55.800
It's a tribute?

10:57.800 --> 10:58.750
Yes. That's exactly what it is.

10:58.800 --> 11:02.750
Weapons party, weapons in the hangar, now!

11:02.800 --> 11:05.750
Weapons party, weapons in the hangar, now!

11:05.800 --> 11:06.800
What?

11:37.800 --> 11:40.750
Ed, have a word. Make
sure he's ready for this.

11:40.800 --> 11:41.750
Sir.

11:41.800 --> 11:45.000
Lance Corporal Armstrong, let's
have a look at that ankle of yours.

11:47.800 --> 11:48.750
The Dhala Road, sir...

11:48.800 --> 11:50.750
Yeah, sometimes it's better to
just get on and do something

11:50.800 --> 11:53.750
and not talk about it.

11:53.800 --> 11:54.800
Sir. Sorry, sir.

11:57.800 --> 12:02.750
Everything I know about soldiering,
I've learned from Orchover.

12:02.800 --> 12:05.750
No harm in asking your
corporal for advice.

12:05.800 --> 12:07.800
OK, men, two minutes to zero hour.

12:08.800 --> 12:11.750
- Does this hurt?
- Yeah.

12:11.800 --> 12:12.750
- Here?
- Yes.

12:12.800 --> 12:15.750
- This?
- Ow!

12:15.800 --> 12:16.750
Well, you're not fit for this.

12:16.800 --> 12:19.800
You're going to have to stay
here and hold the fort with me.

12:21.800 --> 12:23.750
Er, it's not anywhere in
battle-dress regulations,

12:23.800 --> 12:27.750
but there's a convention that one
roll up from the elbow is right.

12:27.800 --> 12:30.750
It's not. It isn't enough.

12:30.800 --> 12:33.750
I go a whole roll higher -- that
takes you clear of the muscle,

12:33.800 --> 12:36.100
then the arm has maximum
freedom of movement.

12:37.800 --> 12:38.750
People laugh at me,

12:38.800 --> 12:42.750
but it can mean a quarter of
a second quicker reloading.

12:42.800 --> 12:44.750
I've seen fatal delay.

12:44.800 --> 12:46.800
I know what a quarter
of a second can mean.

12:53.800 --> 12:54.750
Load up!

13:12.800 --> 13:14.750
It's the reporter.

13:14.800 --> 13:15.900
It's the Seven Dwarves.

13:17.800 --> 13:18.800
Which Jeep am I in?

13:30.800 --> 13:32.100
Yusra, I came to thank you.

13:35.800 --> 13:36.750
I'm alone. You must go.

13:36.800 --> 13:38.750
It's dangerous for me.

13:38.800 --> 13:40.750
Look, if you don't want
me to talk to you again,

13:40.800 --> 13:41.750
just tell me now and I won't.

13:41.800 --> 13:44.800
No-one can know I helped
you escape. Promise me.

14:00.800 --> 14:02.750
How did you know it was a scorpion?

14:02.800 --> 14:05.750
Well, it's always a scorpion,

14:05.800 --> 14:07.800
unless it's a snake.

14:08.800 --> 14:10.750
Oh, I had a snake my first week here.

14:10.800 --> 14:12.750
Where was it?

14:12.800 --> 14:14.400
Oh, you have to check every time.

14:15.800 --> 14:16.750
Where?

14:16.800 --> 14:17.750
Bottom of the bed.

14:24.800 --> 14:25.900
There's a little blood.

14:26.800 --> 14:30.800
You have to push! This
baby has to be born now!

14:42.800 --> 14:44.750
That's it.

14:44.800 --> 14:46.750
There, there. There we
are. The baby's out.

14:46.800 --> 14:47.750
[It's OK.]

14:47.800 --> 14:49.750
Fetch the doctor.

14:50.800 --> 14:52.800
Where's my baby?

14:54.800 --> 14:56.750
Is it all right?

14:58.800 --> 14:59.800
Oh...

15:02.800 --> 15:04.250
This is Mary Markham's.

15:05.800 --> 15:08.750
You should be naked in bed
with your brand-new husband.

15:08.800 --> 15:10.750
There'll be a time for nighties.

15:10.800 --> 15:11.750
Where are they going today?

15:11.800 --> 15:15.750
Upcountry, which is a euphemism.

15:15.800 --> 15:18.750
Well, it's best we don't know too much.

15:18.800 --> 15:19.800
Is that what he said?

15:21.800 --> 15:24.750
In case the NLF kidnap
us, and tie us to a tree,

15:24.800 --> 15:27.750
and take away our virtue, and
force us to tell them battle plans

15:27.800 --> 15:30.750
we've been discussing with our husbands?

15:30.800 --> 15:31.800
Hmm...

15:34.800 --> 15:36.800
Do you love him?

15:38.800 --> 15:39.800
Of course.

15:41.800 --> 15:43.800
In every breath and between every breath?

15:47.800 --> 15:49.800
Yes.

15:58.800 --> 16:00.800
You must love Ed very much.

16:02.800 --> 16:03.800
Why do you say that?

16:06.800 --> 16:09.750
I don't know,

16:09.800 --> 16:11.800
just the way you talk about love.

16:40.800 --> 16:41.750
Quickly, we're coming through!

16:41.800 --> 16:43.750
Ah!

16:43.800 --> 16:44.750
Call him Peter.

16:44.800 --> 16:45.750
- Doctor?
- Yes?

16:45.800 --> 16:47.800
The baby -- Peter.

16:49.800 --> 16:52.750
My husband, Major Markham,

16:52.800 --> 16:53.750
I don't want him worrying.

16:53.800 --> 16:55.750
- Please don't tell him.
- Mmm...

17:18.800 --> 17:19.750
It's only seven miles, Stoneham.

17:19.800 --> 17:21.800
It'll be over before you know it.

17:24.800 --> 17:25.800
You sit up front.

17:33.800 --> 17:34.800
Thank you.

17:41.800 --> 17:43.750
Foot down. Straight ahead.

17:43.800 --> 17:46.000
Don't look at anything
other than the road, OK?

17:47.800 --> 17:48.800
Let's go!

18:27.800 --> 18:29.750
Contact front!

18:41.800 --> 18:42.800
First time?

18:58.800 --> 19:01.750
We're behind time. Mile and a half.

19:01.800 --> 19:03.750
We'll run in. Move!

19:03.800 --> 19:04.900
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

19:08.800 --> 19:10.750
- Are you all right?
- Yes, sir.

19:10.800 --> 19:12.800
So pick it up. Come on. Come on.

19:15.800 --> 19:18.750
- Nine hours, we calculate...
- Sir?

19:18.800 --> 19:20.750
.. that you were out there.

19:20.800 --> 19:21.800
Yes, sir.

19:23.800 --> 19:26.750
Erm... Did anyone help you in any way?

19:26.800 --> 19:27.800
No. Nobody.

19:34.800 --> 19:37.750
You stayed away from people?

19:37.800 --> 19:38.800
That's right.

19:41.800 --> 19:42.750
Good.

19:42.800 --> 19:43.750
Sir, I can't feel my foot...

19:43.800 --> 19:45.800
Oh, no, that's good. You keep it in there.

