25:40.800 --> 25:43.750
Can we get a drink while you two
talk about roads in East Anglia?

25:43.800 --> 25:45.750
The usual, Clive.

25:45.800 --> 25:46.750
Certainly, ma'am.

25:46.800 --> 25:48.750
Oh, a bitter lemon.

25:48.800 --> 25:49.750
With a twist?

25:49.800 --> 25:50.750
Yes, please.

25:50.800 --> 25:53.000
You stick a double in
that and put it on my tab.

26:12.800 --> 26:15.750
I can't seem to stop shivering.

26:15.800 --> 26:19.750
You're cold because that's what
happens when you lose blood.

26:19.800 --> 26:20.800
It's not...

26:21.800 --> 26:22.750
It... It's not...

26:22.800 --> 26:24.800
Could I have a word, Doctor?

26:28.800 --> 26:30.750
Oh...

26:30.800 --> 26:31.750
- It's not stopping.
- I can see that.

26:31.800 --> 26:34.750
- Well, perhaps Colonel Amery...
- No, I can fix this.

26:34.800 --> 26:35.800
How?

26:37.800 --> 26:39.750
Get the anaesthetist. Let's get her under.

26:39.800 --> 26:41.750
- For what?
- Hysterectomy.

26:41.800 --> 26:44.600
- But Colonel Amery...
- Just get the anaesthetist, Nurse.

27:12.800 --> 27:14.800
Take up defensive positions.

27:42.300 --> 27:43.300
It's a Land Rover...

27:46.800 --> 27:48.750
.. not a Jeep.

27:53.800 --> 27:55.750
I could show you around.

27:55.800 --> 27:58.750
Sure. What?

27:58.800 --> 27:59.800
The Land Rover, it...

28:01.800 --> 28:05.750
The door comes off, so when
you're jumping in and out

28:05.800 --> 28:09.800
you don't have to bother about a
door to open and close all the time.

28:16.200 --> 28:17.300
Slow down.

28:26.800 --> 28:28.800
Relieve Orchover, Stoneham.

28:34.800 --> 28:37.750
If anything happens out
here, you're on your own.

28:37.800 --> 28:40.750
We have responsibility for each other,

28:40.800 --> 28:42.800
but not for you.

28:46.800 --> 28:49.750
Thank you.

28:49.800 --> 28:52.750
It makes a change not to be
patronised by a man in uniform,

28:52.800 --> 28:56.750
and it makes my job of reporting
on who you kill and how and why,

28:56.800 --> 28:58.750
so much easier.

29:03.800 --> 29:06.750
And now he wants to
perform a hysterectomy.

29:06.800 --> 29:07.750
Oh. Who's the doctor?

29:07.800 --> 29:09.750
- Dr Rankin.
- Hmm...

29:09.800 --> 29:12.750
It's not lack of experience in
junior doctors that kills patients,

29:12.800 --> 29:14.750
it's pride. Who is she?

29:14.800 --> 29:15.750
Her name's Mary Markham.

29:15.800 --> 29:17.750
- Oh, my God!
- You know her?

29:17.800 --> 29:20.800
- I was at Sandhurst with
Harry Markham. - Oh...

29:21.800 --> 29:22.750
We're in, sir.

29:22.800 --> 29:24.750
- For what?
- Hysterectomy.

29:24.800 --> 29:25.750
- Close her up.
- Sir?

29:25.800 --> 29:28.750
Get me six feet of rolled
bandage, soak it in iodine

29:28.800 --> 29:29.750
and fold it three times.

29:29.800 --> 29:32.750
- Sir... - A big hole in the
groin from a piece of shrapnel

29:32.800 --> 29:33.750
and it wouldn't stop bleeding,

29:33.800 --> 29:36.750
so we packed it tight
with every bandage we had.

29:36.800 --> 29:38.750
I mean, we really jammed it in.

29:40.800 --> 29:44.750
Sergeant Paul Miller in
Malaya, 2nd of June, 1957.

29:44.800 --> 29:47.750
We're going to do the same
thing with Mary Markham.

29:47.800 --> 29:49.800
What are you all looking at? Move.

30:06.800 --> 30:08.750
I'm sure it'll be fine, sir.

30:08.800 --> 30:11.800
I don't like us being in
one place for too long.

30:12.800 --> 30:13.800
I meant Mrs Markham.

30:16.300 --> 30:17.750
Right. Yes, of course.

30:27.800 --> 30:30.750
Do you want a drink with me some time?

30:30.800 --> 30:32.800
Mmm, mmm...

30:44.800 --> 30:48.800
I think the answer's yes... about Joe.

30:49.800 --> 30:51.750
In bed?

30:51.800 --> 30:52.750
Mm-hmm.

30:52.800 --> 30:53.800
Good.

30:56.800 --> 30:57.800
That's good.

30:59.800 --> 31:03.750
Of course, it means
he's had other girls --

31:03.800 --> 31:05.800
dress rehearsals for you.

31:09.800 --> 31:11.800
But you need to be the one.

31:13.800 --> 31:17.750
You need to be surprising,

31:17.800 --> 31:22.800
and unpredictable and profound.

31:34.800 --> 31:36.800
I want you to be happy.

31:47.800 --> 31:48.800
Let's swim.

32:08.800 --> 32:10.000
The bleeding's stopped.

32:14.800 --> 32:17.750
Sergeant Miller in Malaya -- did he live?

32:17.800 --> 32:19.750
The risk of infection is high.

32:19.800 --> 32:21.750
But did he live?

32:21.800 --> 32:23.100
Get her husband here now.

32:26.800 --> 32:29.750
- Understood.
- Thank you, Doctor.

32:29.800 --> 32:32.750
It's Mrs Markham, sir.
She's... It's touch and go.

32:32.800 --> 32:34.750
They've asked for the Major.

32:34.800 --> 32:35.750
Let's go.

32:35.800 --> 32:37.800
Load up!

33:47.800 --> 33:49.800
I'm sorry about Nick Page.

34:03.800 --> 34:05.750
Can you dive?

34:05.800 --> 34:06.800
No.

34:07.800 --> 34:08.800
I'll teach you.

34:12.800 --> 34:13.800
Come on.

34:14.800 --> 34:16.750
Oh, erm...

34:16.800 --> 34:18.750
All right?

34:18.800 --> 34:21.750
- Yeah. Well, what if there's
something in the...? - Arms up.

34:21.800 --> 34:23.650
- Arms up.
- Arms up.

34:24.800 --> 34:27.750
- Head down.
- Oh, no, hold on, how deep is it?

34:27.800 --> 34:28.750
It's deep enough.

34:28.800 --> 34:30.750
- Oh...
- Kick your legs out.

34:30.800 --> 34:32.000
That's all there is to it.

34:37.800 --> 34:38.750
Ah!

34:38.800 --> 34:39.800
Very good.

34:42.800 --> 34:45.750
What are you doing that for?

34:45.800 --> 34:46.750
The sharks don't like it.

34:46.800 --> 34:47.750
- Oh...
- Huh?

34:47.800 --> 34:52.750
Should have a shark net,
really, but stones seem to work.

34:52.800 --> 34:53.800
Oh, Harvey!

35:01.800 --> 35:02.800
Come on.

35:04.800 --> 35:05.800
There we go.

35:07.800 --> 35:08.800
Very graceful.

35:30.800 --> 35:33.800
Alison? Alison!

35:40.800 --> 35:42.300
Whoo!

36:09.800 --> 36:10.800
Ah...

36:15.800 --> 36:17.750
Hey! Armstrong!

36:17.800 --> 36:19.750
Stop, stop, stop!

36:25.800 --> 36:26.800
Sergeant! Sarge...

39:39.800 --> 39:41.750
- Retreat! Fire!
- Fall back!

39:41.800 --> 39:43.750
Enemy fire!

39:43.800 --> 39:46.800
Contact front. Fall back to the AOP.

39:58.800 --> 40:00.750
Sir, we should go and find them.

40:00.800 --> 40:01.800
Not our orders.

40:03.800 --> 40:05.750
What if they've got Starfish

40:05.800 --> 40:07.800
and they make it back here and we're gone?

40:17.800 --> 40:19.750
- Man down!
- Man down!

40:23.800 --> 40:25.750
- Contact rear!
- Contact rear!

40:36.800 --> 40:38.750
Dimarco, move!

40:39.800 --> 40:41.300
Right flanking!

40:44.300 --> 40:47.750
Go! Move! Move!

40:50.800 --> 40:51.800
Let's go.

40:54.800 --> 40:56.750
Re-org! Re-org on me!

40:56.800 --> 40:58.750
Re-org! Re-org!

40:58.800 --> 40:59.750
Move! Move!

40:59.800 --> 41:01.800
Ready, ready, ready!

41:04.800 --> 41:07.750
We've got to move. We've got
to move or we'll die here.

41:11.800 --> 41:12.800
Shit.

41:15.800 --> 41:17.750
Cliff! Dimarco, move!

41:17.800 --> 41:18.800
Go, go, go!

41:34.800 --> 41:36.800
Oh, God.

41:38.800 --> 41:39.750
Ready.

41:39.800 --> 41:41.800
- One at a time, go!
- Sir.

41:51.800 --> 41:54.750
Climb fast. Don't stop. Don't think.

41:54.800 --> 41:55.750
- Sir?
- Dimarco...

41:55.800 --> 41:57.750
I... Look, I don't know how to say this...

41:57.800 --> 41:58.750
What is it?

41:58.800 --> 42:00.800
I'm... I'm frightened of heights, sir.

42:08.800 --> 42:09.800
Who the hell is that?

42:12.800 --> 42:13.800
Halt!

42:16.800 --> 42:18.750
- Sir...
- Yes.

42:18.800 --> 42:21.600
It's your wife. You need to
turn around and come back now.

42:21.800 --> 42:22.750
Just don't look down.

42:22.800 --> 42:24.750
~

42:24.800 --> 42:25.900
Climb, and don't look...

42:27.700 --> 42:28.350
Sir!

42:30.800 --> 42:31.800
Shit...

42:59.800 --> 43:00.800
Captain...

43:12.800 --> 43:15.750
I can't make this decision...

43:15.800 --> 43:18.750
.. choosing between my wife and my men...

43:18.800 --> 43:19.800
I understand.

43:20.800 --> 43:22.800
You have to make it for me.

43:28.800 --> 43:30.750
We can't leave them out there.

43:30.800 --> 43:33.750
Mary Markham is being looked after.

43:33.800 --> 43:34.750
Let's go.

43:45.800 --> 43:48.750
Ugh, come on...

43:49.800 --> 43:52.800
~

43:55.800 --> 43:57.750
~

44:05.800 --> 44:07.750
~

44:07.800 --> 44:09.750
Stop!

44:09.800 --> 44:11.750
No!

44:11.800 --> 44:12.750
Mercy!

44:44.800 --> 44:45.800
Do you believe in God?

44:49.800 --> 44:50.800
Yes.

44:53.800 --> 44:54.800
Good.

44:58.800 --> 44:59.800
Pray.

45:10.800 --> 45:16.750
Our Father, who art in heaven,

45:16.800 --> 45:18.800
hallowed be thy name.

45:23.800 --> 45:27.750
Thy kingdom come,

45:27.800 --> 45:29.750
thy will be done,

45:29.800 --> 45:32.750
on earth, as it is in heaven.

45:37.800 --> 45:42.750
Give us this day

45:42.800 --> 45:46.750
our daily bread,

45:46.800 --> 45:51.750
and forgive us our trespasses,

45:51.800 --> 45:55.800
as we forgive those who
trespass against us...

46:00.800 --> 46:05.750
.. and lead us not into temptation,

46:05.800 --> 46:10.750
but deliver us from evil,

46:10.800 --> 46:14.750
for thine is the kingdom --

46:14.800 --> 46:21.800
the power and the glory are
yours forever and ever.

46:26.800 --> 46:27.800
Amen.

46:42.800 --> 46:45.800
Sir, it's Dimarco...

46:59.800 --> 47:00.750
You can't do that.

47:00.800 --> 47:02.800
It's my job.

47:04.800 --> 47:06.750
They knew. They know.

47:06.800 --> 47:07.750
It's there for us to see.

47:07.800 --> 47:09.800
It might be an ambush.

47:11.800 --> 47:14.750
Sir, we should do something. Sir?

47:14.800 --> 47:15.750
Miss Franklin!

47:15.800 --> 47:17.800
Miss Franklin...

47:18.800 --> 47:19.800
~

47:40.800 --> 47:42.750
(Christ...) Baxter, no!

47:42.800 --> 47:45.800
Don't touch it, Sergeant
-- it may be booby-trapped.

47:52.800 --> 47:53.900
~

49:54.800 --> 49:56.750
If you were to apply
for compassionate leave,

49:56.800 --> 50:00.800
you'd probably get it, because
you'd be applying to me.

50:10.800 --> 50:12.800
He fought in the Great War, your father?

50:13.800 --> 50:15.800
He doesn't like to talk about it.

50:18.800 --> 50:20.800
Men don't.

50:27.800 --> 50:30.800
There's a photograph of him, in uniform.

50:33.800 --> 50:34.800
He looks...

50:35.800 --> 50:37.800
.. like a...

50:38.800 --> 50:40.800
.. proper soldier.

50:42.800 --> 50:43.750
Perhaps you could show it to me sometime.

50:43.800 --> 50:45.800
I don't have it any more.

50:51.800 --> 50:53.750
But...

50:53.800 --> 50:57.750
.. you could talk to him,
couldn't you? Have you ever...

50:57.800 --> 50:59.800
.. talked to him about it?

51:32.800 --> 51:35.000
- I'll drive you to the hospital, sir.
- Thank you.

51:53.800 --> 51:56.800
Your father likes your
hair combed this way.

51:58.800 --> 51:59.800
Perfect.

52:02.800 --> 52:04.750
Oh, George!

52:06.800 --> 52:08.800
Daddy's coming! Daddy!

52:13.800 --> 52:15.800
Dad! Daddy!

52:22.800 --> 52:24.750
He's going to see your new baby brother.

52:24.800 --> 52:26.800
But he promised.

52:41.800 --> 52:42.800
~

52:45.800 --> 52:50.750
I've been learning Arabic,
and my dresses are here.

52:50.800 --> 52:51.750
Have you been drinking?

52:51.800 --> 52:53.750
A little. Oh, Joe, there's
a most wonderful club.

52:53.800 --> 52:54.750
Who did you go with?

52:54.800 --> 52:57.750
Alison Laithwaite. She's a friend already.

52:57.800 --> 52:59.800
- She can't be.
- What? Why?

53:01.800 --> 53:05.750
Her husband is not an easy man,
and I'm superior in rank to him.

53:05.800 --> 53:08.750
- Well, you can sort that out.
- Not if my wife is undermining me!

53:08.800 --> 53:11.750
- What do you mean? - Through her
relationship with Alison Laithwaite.

53:11.800 --> 53:14.800
- Alison doesn't care about
that kind of thing. - I do!

53:15.800 --> 53:16.800
I care.

53:23.800 --> 53:27.000
And it isn't Alison Laithwaite
who's putting her life on the line.

53:34.800 --> 53:39.750
♪ Silent night

53:39.800 --> 53:44.750
♪ Holy night

53:44.800 --> 53:48.750
♪ All is calm

53:48.800 --> 53:53.750
♪ All is bright

53:53.800 --> 54:01.800
♪ Proud young virgin, mother and child

54:02.800 --> 54:10.800
♪ Holy infant, so tender and mild... ♪

54:13.800 --> 54:15.750
Hello, Major. Can I help you?

54:15.800 --> 54:16.900
I'm looking for my wife.

54:19.300 --> 54:21.750
- And the mortuary.
- Right this way.

54:21.800 --> 54:27.800
♪ Sleep in heavenly peace. ♪

55:08.800 --> 55:10.800
Peter, this is Daddy.

55:14.800 --> 55:16.800
Hello, Peter.

55:21.800 --> 55:25.800
There. That's your lovely daddy.

55:36.800 --> 55:37.800
Oh, Peter.

55:43.800 --> 55:44.800
Hello, Dad.

55:45.800 --> 55:47.800
It's Alex. It's your son.

55:50.800 --> 55:52.800
Dad, do you mind if I
ask you a few questions?

55:56.800 --> 55:59.800
Yeah. Yeah, I do, I remember.
The old songs, yeah.

56:00.800 --> 56:02.800
You first?

56:05.800 --> 56:09.800
♪ There was a soldier, a Scottish soldier

56:12.800 --> 56:16.750
♪ Who wandered far away,
and soldiered far away... ♪

56:35.800 --> 56:37.800
I saw a shooting star.

56:41.800 --> 56:43.750
They're dead.

56:43.800 --> 56:45.100
That's what you're seeing.

56:47.800 --> 56:49.800
A death.

57:01.800 --> 57:02.800
I'll get you another.

57:17.800 --> 57:20.750
- You must be missing him terribly.
- Ed, you don't have to do this.

57:20.800 --> 57:22.750
You don't have anyone else to talk to.

57:22.800 --> 57:24.750
Your wife, she's embarrassing herself.

57:24.800 --> 57:26.750
- And you.
- I'm not embarrassed.

57:26.800 --> 57:29.750
About that reporter -- the world
cannot see the photographs she took.

57:29.800 --> 57:31.750
~

57:31.800 --> 57:33.800
- Why are you here?
- Because I like you.

57:35.800 --> 57:37.750
- Are you disobeying my order?
- Yes, sir, I am.

57:37.800 --> 57:39.750
After all we've been though,

57:39.800 --> 57:42.750
and who we've lost, I want to make
this Christmas one to remember.

57:42.800 --> 57:44.750
Oh, God!

